<h3 class="gamma text-center light rhythm-2">Visual Mockups</h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</header>

<div class="row rhythm-2">
<div class="large-9 medium-10 small-11 small-centered columns">
<p class="lead">We still needed to document details of the application that we didn’t have time to include in the prototype, in order to ensure the developers had a visual roadmap. After the process of style patterning and mechanical prototyping, we were able produce much more informed documentation. </p>

<p>We were able to leverage output from our time "in-browser", and focus on defining a level of fidelity that Photoshop excels at. Depending on the context, we used the tool that immediately allowed us to produce the most valuable artifact for the product. </p>
</div>

<div class="large-12 columns">
<figure>
<img src="images/responsive3.jpg">
<figcaption class="large-9 large-centered columns">
<p>Rather than rely on visual mockups in the beginning, we used them to detail nuances as well as dynamic states within the application.</p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>

<div class="large-12 columns">
<figure>
<img src="images/pattern1.jpg">
<figcaption class="large-9 large-centered columns">
<p>Users on different devices are served different UI elements and feature sets based on their device. All of this is running off the same set of templates.</p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>

